# Benchmarking F# 101

This is some simple code I put together to illustrate how to do basic benchmarking with F#.

I was befuddled by the results of the different looping constructs (`for .. = .. to` versus `for .. in`). I expected one to be faster than the others and I got the opposite result. Since then I have looked at the assembly and can see that the resulting x86 is faster but I haven't figured out why yet. The is the goal of my next recording and post.

Assembly results are [here](https://sharplab.io/#v2:) on SharbLab for those interested.
